h3cEntityExtend.name: h3cEntityExtend
h3cEntityExtend.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip: 100085
h3cEntityExtend.description: The private MIB file includes the general extent information of the device.

H3cAdminState.name: H3cAdminState
H3cAdminState.description: The administrative state for this object, and it is possible to set the state when needed. A value of locked means the resource is administratively prohibited from use. A value of shuttingDown means that usage is administratively limited to current instances of use. A value of unlocked means the resource is not administratively prohibited from use.
H3cAdminState.reference: ITU Recommendation X.731, 'Information Technology - Open Systems Interconnection - System Management: State Management Function', 1992

H3cOperState.name: H3cOperState
H3cOperState.description: Represents the possible values of operational states. A value of disabled means the resource is totally inoperable. A value of enabled means the resource is partially or fully operable.
H3cOperState.reference: ITU Recommendation X.731, 'Information Technology - Open Systems Interconnection - System Management: State Management Function', 1992

H3cAlarmStatus.name: H3cAlarmStatus
H3cAlarmStatus.description: Represents the possible values of alarm status. When no bits of this attribute are set, then none of the status conditions described below are present. When the value of under repair is set, the resource is currently being repaired. When the value of critical is set, one or more critical alarms are active against the resource. When the value of major is set, one or more major alarms are active against the resource. When the value of minor is set, one or more minor alarms are active against the resource. When the value of warning is set, one or more warning alarms are active against the resource. When the value of indeterminate is set, one or more alarms of indeterminate severity are active against the resource. When the value of alarm outstanding is set, one or more alarms is active against the resource. The fault may or may not be disabling.
H3cAlarmStatus.reference: ITU Recommendation X.731, 'Information Technology - Open Systems Interconnection - System Management: State Management Function', 1992

H3cStandbyStatus.name: H3cStandbyStatus
H3cStandbyStatus.description: Represents the possible values of standby status. A value of hotStandby means the resource is not providing service, but is will be immediately able to take over the role of the resource to be backed-up, without the need for initialization activity, and will contain the same information as the resource to be backed up. A value of coldStandy means that the resource is to back-up another resource, but will not be immediately able to take over the role of a resource to be backed up, and will require some initialization activity. A value of providingService means the resource is providing service.
H3cStandbyStatus.reference: ITU Recommendation X.731, 'Information Technology - Open Systems Interconnection - System Management: State Management Function', 1992

h3cEntityExtStateTable.name: h3cEntityExtStateTable
h3cEntityExtStateTable.description: This table contains one row per physical entity, There is always at least one row for an 'overall' physical entity. The information in each row may be not include all the object in this table, because of the entity need not some of the information here.

h3cEntityExtStateEntry.name: h3cEntityExtStateEntry
h3cEntityExtStateEntry.description: The information about a particular physical entity.

h3cEntityExtPhysicalIndex.name: h3cEntityExtPhysicalIndex
h3cEntityExtPhysicalIndex.description: The index of h3cEntityExtStateTable. This index is identical to entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB

h3cEntityExtAdminStatus.name: h3cEntityExtAdminStatus
h3cEntityExtAdminStatus.description: The administrative state for this object.

h3cEntityExtOperStatus.name: h3cEntityExtOperStatus
h3cEntityExtOperStatus.description: The operate state for this object.

h3cEntityExtStandbyStatus.name: h3cEntityExtStandbyStatus
h3cEntityExtStandbyStatus.description: This object is used for monitoring standby status. Not all entities support this object.

h3cEntityExtAlarmLight.name: h3cEntityExtAlarmLight
h3cEntityExtAlarmLight.description: The alarm status for this entity. It does not include the severity of alarms raised on child components. In this condition, there will be a alarm light on the entity, the object should have the same status with it.

h3cEntityExtCpuUsage.name: h3cEntityExtCpuUsage
h3cEntityExtCpuUsage.description: The CPU usage for this entity. Generally, the CPU usage will calculate the overall CPU usage on the entity, and it is not sensible with the number of CPU on the entity.

h3cEntityExtCpuUsageThreshold.name: h3cEntityExtCpuUsageThreshold
h3cEntityExtCpuUsageThreshold.description: The threshold for the CPU usage. When the CPU usage exceeds the threshold, a notification will be sent.

h3cEntityExtMemUsage.name: h3cEntityExtMemUsage
h3cEntityExtMemUsage.description: The memory usage for the entity. This object indicates what percent of memory are used.

h3cEntityExtMemUsageThreshold.name: h3cEntityExtMemUsageThreshold
h3cEntityExtMemUsageThreshold.description: The threshold for the Memory usage, When the memory usage exceeds the threshold, a notification will be sent.

h3cEntityExtMemSize.name: h3cEntityExtMemSize
h3cEntityExtMemSize.description: The size of memory for the entity.

h3cEntityExtUpTime.name: h3cEntityExtUpTime
h3cEntityExtUpTime.description: The uptime for the entity. The meaning of uptime is when the entity is up, and the value of the object will add 1 seconds while the entity is running.

h3cEntityExtTemperatureThreshold.name: h3cEntityExtTemperatureThreshold
h3cEntityExtTemperatureThreshold.description: The threshold for the temperature. When the temperature exceeds the threshold, a notification will be sent.

h3cEntityExtVoltageLowThreshold.name: h3cEntityExtVoltageLowThreshold
h3cEntityExtVoltageLowThreshold.description: The low-threshold for the voltage. When voltage is lower than low-threshold, a notification will be sent.

h3cEntityExtVoltageHighThreshold.name: h3cEntityExtVoltageHighThreshold
h3cEntityExtVoltageHighThreshold.description: The high-threshold for the voltage. When voltage greater than high-threshold, a notification will be sent.

h3cEntityExtCriticalTemperatureThreshold.name: h3cEntityExtCriticalTemperatureThreshold
h3cEntityExtCriticalTemperatureThreshold.description: The threshold for the critical Temperature. When temperature exceeds the critical temperature, a notification will be sent.

h3cEntityExtErrorStatus.name: h3cEntityExtErrorStatus
h3cEntityExtErrorStatus.description: Indicate the error state of this entity object. Now it only supports Port, general power supply, RPS power supply and board/Subcard. It may have one of these values. The following four values can be used for all kinds of entities. notSupported(1) means this entity can not support this function. normal(2) means the statement of this entity is normal. for ports, it doesn't differentiate 10M/s, 100M/s, 1000M/s, duplex and half-duplex. For fan, power supply and board-Subcard, it means their states are normal. postFailure(3) means the entity fails to POST. entityAbsent(4) means the entity is absent now. The following values is depended on the entity . For Port entities, it may have the following values. If its POST is failure, then the value of the instance will be postFailure(3), otherwise the value will be normal(2). If enable power supply over Ethernet on this port is failure, the value of this instance will be poeError(11), otherwise it will be normal(2). For stack port, if it connects to another stack port normally, and these two units merge into one stack, then the value of this instance will be normal(2). If something wrong occurs and the unit can not merge into stack, the value of this instance will be stackPortFailed(23). If the stack port forms resilient daisy chain with another stack port on the other unit, the value of this instance will be stackPortBlocked(22). For SFP ports, if it fail to receive, the value of this instance will be sfpRecvError(31), if it fail to send, the value is sfpSendError(32), if it fail to send and receive, the value is sfpBothError(33), otherwise it will be normal(2). fanError(41) means that the fan stops working. psuError(51) means that the Power Supply Unit is in the state of fault. rpsError(61) means the RPS is in the state of fault. moduleFaulty(71) means the Module is in the state of fault. sensorError(81) means the sensor is in the state of fault. hardwareFaulty(91) means the hardware of specified entity is in the state of fault. NMS must be compatible with the states which may be added in the future.

h3cEntityExtCpuMaxUsage.name: h3cEntityExtCpuMaxUsage
h3cEntityExtCpuMaxUsage.description: The maximal CPU usage for the entity in the period of time.

h3cEntityExtLowerTemperatureThreshold.name: h3cEntityExtLowerTemperatureThreshold
h3cEntityExtLowerTemperatureThreshold.description: The threshold for the lower Temperature. When temperature runs under the threshold, a notification will be sent.

h3cEntityExtShutdownTemperatureThreshold.name: h3cEntityExtShutdownTemperatureThreshold
h3cEntityExtShutdownTemperatureThreshold.description: The threshold for the shutdown Temperature. When temperature exceeds the threshold, a notification will be sent and the entity will be shutdown.

h3cEntityExtPhyMemSize.name: h3cEntityExtPhyMemSize
h3cEntityExtPhyMemSize.description: The memory size of entity. This is the physical attribute of entity.

h3cEntityExtPhyCpuFrequency.name: h3cEntityExtPhyCpuFrequency
h3cEntityExtPhyCpuFrequency.description: The CPU frequency of entity. Unit of measure is MHZ.

h3cEntityExtFirstUsedDate.name: h3cEntityExtFirstUsedDate
h3cEntityExtFirstUsedDate.description: The first used date of the entity.

h3cEntityExtCpuAvgUsage.name: h3cEntityExtCpuAvgUsage
h3cEntityExtCpuAvgUsage.description: The average CPU usage for the entity in a period of time.

h3cEntityExtMemAvgUsage.name: h3cEntityExtMemAvgUsage
h3cEntityExtMemAvgUsage.description: The average memory usage for the entity in a period of time.

h3cEntityExtCriticalLowerTemperatureThre.name: h3cEntityExtCriticalLowerTemperatureThreshold
h3cEntityExtCriticalLowerTemperatureThre.description: The threshold for the critical Temperature. When temperature exceeds the critical lower temperature, a notification will be sent.

h3cEntityExtShutdownLowerTemperatureThre.name: h3cEntityExtShutdownLowerTemperatureThreshold
h3cEntityExtShutdownLowerTemperatureThre.description: The threshold for the shutdown Temperature. When temperature exceeds the lower threshold, a notification will be sent and the entity will be shutdown.

h3cEntityExtCpuUsageRecoverThreshold.name: h3cEntityExtCpuUsageRecoverThreshold
h3cEntityExtCpuUsageRecoverThreshold.description: The recover threshold for the CPU usage. When the CPU usage falls down to the threshold, a notification is sent. The h3cEntityExtCpuUsageRecoverThreshold must be less than or equal to the h3cEntityExtCpuUsageThreshold.

h3cEntityExtManuTable.name: h3cEntityExtManuTable
h3cEntityExtManuTable.description: The table about device manufacture information.

h3cEntityExtManuEntry.name: h3cEntityExtManuEntry
h3cEntityExtManuEntry.description: The device manufacture information about a particular physical entity.

h3cEntityExtManuPhysicalIndex.name: h3cEntityExtManuPhysicalIndex
h3cEntityExtManuPhysicalIndex.description: The index of h3cEntityExtManuTable. This index is identical to entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB.

h3cEntityExtManuSerialNum.name: h3cEntityExtManuSerialNum
h3cEntityExtManuSerialNum.description: Manufacture serial number. The manufacture serial number of the entity such as chassis, module, and so on. It is got from the device when manufacturing. For low level box-device, the manufacture serial number is the device-number of System Control Board(SCB for short), it is written into the SCB directly; for middle level or high level frame-device, the manufacture serial number is the device-numbers of SCB and Service Board, because the SCB, Service Board and chassis are separate to sale and the device-number of chassis can not be written into board.

h3cEntityExtManuBuildInfo.name: h3cEntityExtManuBuildInfo
h3cEntityExtManuBuildInfo.description: Device version information. The device version information of the entity such as chassis, module, and so on. It consists of software version information and hardware version information.

h3cEntityExtManuBOM.name: h3cEntityExtManuBOM
h3cEntityExtManuBOM.description: Device BOM code. The device BOM code of the entity such as chassis, module, and so on. It is the component code of ERP system, which can be disassembled from device-number.

h3cEntityExtMacAddressCount.name: h3cEntityExtMacAddressCount
h3cEntityExtMacAddressCount.description: MAC address count. The count of MAC addresses of the entity, such as chassis, module, or port, and so on.

h3cEntityExtPowerTable.name: h3cEntityExtPowerTable
h3cEntityExtPowerTable.description: This table describes the power information of all the physical entity on the device, such as the fans, the subcards, the boards, etc.

h3cEntityExtPowerEntry.name: h3cEntityExtPowerEntry
h3cEntityExtPowerEntry.description: The entity power information about a particular physical entity.

h3cEntityExtPowerPhysicalIndex.name: h3cEntityExtPowerPhysicalIndex
h3cEntityExtPowerPhysicalIndex.description: The index of h3cEntityExtPowerTable. This index is identical to entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB.

h3cEntityExtNominalPower.name: h3cEntityExtNominalPower
h3cEntityExtNominalPower.description: The nominal power of the entity expressed in milliWatts.

h3cEntityExtCurrentPower.name: h3cEntityExtCurrentPower
h3cEntityExtCurrentPower.description: The measured usage power of the entity expressed in milliWatts.

h3cEntityExtAveragePower.name: h3cEntityExtAveragePower
h3cEntityExtAveragePower.description: The average power consumed by the entity expressed in milliWatts. Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has no effect on its value and an error is returned.

h3cEntityExtPeakPower.name: h3cEntityExtPeakPower
h3cEntityExtPeakPower.description: The peak power consumed by the entity expressed in milliWatts. Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has no effect on its value and an error is returned.

h3cProcessTable.name: h3cProcessTable
h3cProcessTable.description: The Table describes the information about a particular process, namely a task.

h3cProcessEntry.name: h3cProcessEntry
h3cProcessEntry.description: The information about a particular process, namely a task.

h3cProcessID.name: h3cProcessID
h3cProcessID.description: This object indicates the identifier of process, namely task ID in system.

h3cProcessName.name: h3cProcessName
h3cProcessName.description: This object indicates the process name.

h3cProcessUtil5Min.name: h3cProcessUtil5Min
h3cProcessUtil5Min.description: This object provides a general idea of how busy a process caused the processor to be over a 5 minute period. The ratio is calculated by the overall CPU usage caused by the process.

h3cEntityExtTemperatureThresholdNotifica.name: h3cEntityExtTemperatureThresholdNotification
h3cEntityExtTemperatureThresholdNotifica.description: The h3cEntityExtTemperatureThresholdNotification indicates the temperature exceeded the threshold. In this condition, user should check the status and the environment of the entity, sometimes it happens because of the failure of air-condition.

h3cEntityExtVoltageLowThresholdNotificat.name: h3cEntityExtVoltageLowThresholdNotification
h3cEntityExtVoltageLowThresholdNotificat.description: The h3cEntityExtVoltageLowThresholdNotification indicates the voltage is lower than the threshold. If the voltage is lower too much than the entity needs, the entity will halt.

h3cEntityExtVoltageHighThresholdNotifica.name: h3cEntityExtVoltageHighThresholdNotification
h3cEntityExtVoltageHighThresholdNotifica.description: The h3cEntityExtVoltageHighThresholdNotification indicates the voltage is higher than the threshold. If the voltage is higher too much than the entity needs, The entity may be damaged by the high voltage.

h3cEntityExtCpuUsageThresholdNotfication.name: h3cEntityExtCpuUsageThresholdNotfication
h3cEntityExtCpuUsageThresholdNotfication.description: The h3cEntityExtCpuUsageThresholdNotfication indicates the entity is overloaded.

h3cEntityExtMemUsageThresholdNotificatio.name: h3cEntityExtMemUsageThresholdNotification
h3cEntityExtMemUsageThresholdNotificatio.description: The h3cEntityExtMemUsageThresholdNotification indicates the entity is overloaded.

h3cEntityExtOperEnabled.name: h3cEntityExtOperEnabled
h3cEntityExtOperEnabled.description: The trap indicates the entity is operable at present.

h3cEntityExtOperDisabled.name: h3cEntityExtOperDisabled
h3cEntityExtOperDisabled.description: The trap indicates the entity is not operable at present.

h3cEntityExtCriticalTemperatureThreshold.name: h3cEntityExtCriticalTemperatureThresholdNotification
h3cEntityExtCriticalTemperatureThreshold.description: The h3cEntityExtCriticalTemperatureThresholdNotification indicates the temperature exceeds the critical temperature. In this condition, user should check the status and the environment of the entity, sometimes it happens because of the failure of air-condition.

h3cEntityExtSFPAlarmOn.name: h3cEntityExtSFPAlarmOn
h3cEntityExtSFPAlarmOn.description: The trap is generated when the SFP module fails or runs abnormally for some particular reason.

h3cEntityExtSFPAlarmOff.name: h3cEntityExtSFPAlarmOff
h3cEntityExtSFPAlarmOff.description: The trap is generated when the SFP module restores to normal status.

h3cEntityExtSFPPhony.name: h3cEntityExtSFPPhony
h3cEntityExtSFPPhony.description: This module is NOT sold by authorized manufacturer. The normal function of the device or assume the maintenance responsibility thereof will NOT be guaranteed. The trap is generated periodically after a phony module has been found.

h3cEntityInsert.name: h3cEntityInsert
h3cEntityInsert.description: The trap is generated when a removeable entity inserting to device.

h3cEntityRemove.name: h3cEntityRemove
h3cEntityRemove.description: The trap is generated when a removeable entity removing from device.

h3cEntityExtForcedPowerOff.name: h3cEntityExtForcedPowerOff
h3cEntityExtForcedPowerOff.description: The trap indicates the entity is forced to power off.

h3cEntityExtForcedPowerOn.name: h3cEntityExtForcedPowerOn
h3cEntityExtForcedPowerOn.description: The trap indicates the entity is forced to power on.

h3cEntityExtFaultAlarmOn.name: h3cEntityExtFaultAlarmOn
h3cEntityExtFaultAlarmOn.description: The trap indicates a fault occures on the specified entity.

h3cEntityExtFaultAlarmOff.name: h3cEntityExtFaultAlarmOff
h3cEntityExtFaultAlarmOff.description: The trap indicates a fault disappears on the specified entity.

h3cEntityExtResourceLack.name: h3cEntityExtResourceLack
h3cEntityExtResourceLack.description: The trap indicates that a kind of resource is not enough on the specified entity.

h3cEntityExtResourceEnough.name: h3cEntityExtResourceEnough
h3cEntityExtResourceEnough.description: The trap indicates that the entity recovers from the status of no enough resource.

h3cEntityExtTemperatureLower.name: h3cEntityExtTemperatureLower
h3cEntityExtTemperatureLower.description: The trap indicates the temperature of a specified entity is under the lower threshold. In this condition, user should check the status and the environment of the entity, sometimes it goes wrong for some reason.

h3cEntityExtTemperatureTooUp.name: h3cEntityExtTemperatureTooUp
h3cEntityExtTemperatureTooUp.description: The trap indicates the temperature of a specified entity exceeded the shutdown threshold. In this condition, user should check the status and the environment of the entity, sometimes it goes wrong for some reason.

h3cEntityExtTemperatureNormal.name: h3cEntityExtTemperatureNormal
h3cEntityExtTemperatureNormal.description: The trap indicates the temperature of a specified entity recover from abnormal status.

h3cEntityExternalAlarmOccur.name: h3cEntityExternalAlarmOccur
h3cEntityExternalAlarmOccur.description: The trap is generated when the monitored device connected to the specified entity fails.

h3cEntityExternalAlarmRecover.name: h3cEntityExternalAlarmRecover
h3cEntityExternalAlarmRecover.description: The trap is generated when the failed device connected to the specified entity returns to normal.

h3cEntityExtCpuUsageThresholdRecover.name: h3cEntityExtCpuUsageThresholdRecover
h3cEntityExtCpuUsageThresholdRecover.description: The trap indicates the CPU usage descends the threshold.

h3cEntityExtMemUsageThresholdRecover.name: h3cEntityExtMemUsageThresholdRecover
h3cEntityExtMemUsageThresholdRecover.description: The trap indicates the memory usage descends the threshold.

h3cEntityExtMemAllocatedFailed.name: h3cEntityExtMemAllocatedFailed
h3cEntityExtMemAllocatedFailed.description: The trap indicates the memory allocated failed.

h3cEntityExtECCParityAlarm.name: h3cEntityExtECCParityAlarm
h3cEntityExtECCParityAlarm.description: The trap indicates the ECC(Error Correction Code) parity error alarm.

h3cEntityExtCritLowerTempThresholdNotifi.name: h3cEntityExtCritLowerTempThresholdNotification
h3cEntityExtCritLowerTempThresholdNotifi.description: The h3cEntityExtCritLowerTempThresholdNotification indicates the temperature is lower than the threshold. If the temperature is lower too much than the entity needs, the entity will halt.

h3cEntityExtTemperatureTooLow.name: h3cEntityExtTemperatureTooLow
h3cEntityExtTemperatureTooLow.description: The h3cEntityExtTemperatureTooLow indicates the temperature is lower than the threshold. If the temperature is lower too much than the entity needs, the entity halts now.

h3cEntityExtFanDirectionNotPreferred.name: h3cEntityExtFanDirectionNotPreferred
h3cEntityExtFanDirectionNotPreferred.description: This trap indicates the specified fan's direction does not accord with preferred. The two parameters indicate the entity index and physical name of fan.

h3cEntityExtFanDirectionNotAccord.name: h3cEntityExtFanDirectionNotAccord
h3cEntityExtFanDirectionNotAccord.description: This trap indicates the direction of fans does not accord with each other. The two parameters indicate the parent entity of the fans.

h3cEntityExtSFPInvalid.name: h3cEntityExtSFPInvalid
h3cEntityExtSFPInvalid.description: The transceiver module is not compatible with the interface card. The authorized manufacturer therefore shall NOT guarantee the normal function of the transceiver. The transceiver module will be invalidated in days. Please replace it with a compatible one as soon as possible. The trap is generated periodically after a phony transceiver module has been found.

h3cEntityExtSFPInvalidNow.name: h3cEntityExtSFPInvalidNow
h3cEntityExtSFPInvalidNow.description: This transceiver module is not compatible with the interface card. The authorized manufacturer therefore shall NOT guarantee the normal function of the transceiver. The trap is generated after a phony transceiver module has been found.

h3cEntityExtSFPInvalidInDays.name: h3cEntityExtSFPInvalidInDays
h3cEntityExtSFPInvalidInDays.description: The days when the transceiver module is still valid, but after those days, it will be invaldated.

h3cEntityExtCompliance.name: h3cEntityExtCompliance
h3cEntityExtCompliance.description: The compliance statement for systems supporting this MIB.
